name: Bird of Paradise
description: Birds of Paradise are native to South Africa. Birds of Paradise bloom from September through May. The flowers of the Birds of Paradise resemble a brightly colored bird in flight and so the name Birds of Paradis

name: Heliconia
description: Heliconia, derived from the Greek word helikonios, is a genus of flowering plants in the Heliconiaceae. Most of the ca 194 known species are native to the tropical Americas, but a few are indigenous to certain islands of the western Pacific and Maluku.

name: Pink Vanda Blooms
description: Vanda orchids produce some of the most magnificent flowers in the world. As a result, they are ranked among the top five genera in horticulture.

name: White Anthurium
description: Anthurium grows in many forms, mostly evergreen, bushy or climbing epiphytes. Some are only found in association with arboreal ant colonies or growing on rocks in midstream (such as A. amnicola).

name: Purple Tulip Shaped Anthurium
description: The stems are short to elongate with a length between 15 and 30 cm. The simple leaves come in many shapes. Most leaves are to be found at the end of the stem. They can be spatulate, rounded, or obtuse at the apex.

name: Yellow Heliconia Caribaea
description: The flowers of this species are actually highly modified leaves and bracts in the shapes of a lobster claws and a deep, rich red color. Heliconia caribea has two arcs of air canals in leaf axis, raphide sacs, five fertile stamens, lateral stamens of inner and outer whorls fertile and no perisperm.

name: Rattlesnake Calathea
description: Rattlesnake Plant (Calathea lancifolia) One of the very best indoor ornamental houseplants, Rattlesnake Calathea has long, medium green leaves with dark decorative spots.
